Neurofluxation 11/29/2022 9:35 AM
There is already a wealth of tutorials available online for the "core" or "QT" wallet. The UI for the core wallet (aka. QT Wallet) is a standard UI that 99% of altcoins use @Happyowl - It's just the way it is. It sounds like you would do well to watch a tutorial on QT wallet usage. The only real difference is the "asset" options for NFTs. For that you can search "How to use Ravencoin core wallet" as their wallet is identical to ours. You can send from a particular address by selecting the Inputs... button in the send tab. The QT wallet is not very "noob friendly" I agree, but it is a wallet that 99.9% of all cryptocurrencies use to some extent. We have a version 2 of the "Purse" web wallet being released later on today and there is "The Kitty" wallet also in the works. Note that for mining it is always best to use the core wallet. (edited)

Ghost089 04/11/2023 8:57 PM
Empawrium is triple pinned. 1 on a hosted service as the primary pin. 2) On JustNFT's primary pin service. 3) On JustNFTs backup private server.
21:03
Any inbound file to Empawrium gets pinned and put into IPFS. At that point, it exists. Even if a service was to shutdown, the asset images we pull and the database information are property of Meowcoin, we do not hold any customer data back from our clients. So, they could easily spin up their own, or in junction w/ another partner an IPFS node and shoot the hashes or raw images into a node and they would repin, since they are the same core files of the hash.
21:03
I use the term, 'property' loosely.
